external_knowledge:
- "Top-performing players" refers to players with the highest average yards rushed, passed, and received per game;
- "Conference and division" refers to the league structure where teams are grouped;
- The rankings are based on the sum of yards rushed, passed, and received, normalized by the number of games played.

- "Average yards per game" is calculated by dividing the total yards by the number of games played;
- "Total tackles" include both solo and assisted tackles;
- The query focuses on the most relevant statistics to provide a clear overview of each player's performance.

sql:
SELECT AVG(T1.yards_rushed) AS average_yards_rushed
FROM (
  SELECT player_id, AVG(yards_rushed) AS yards_rushed
  FROM player_game_statistics
  GROUP BY player_id
) T1
WHERE T1.yards_rushed > (
  SELECT AVG(yards_rushed)
  FROM player_game_statistics
);

